To distinguish between converted and unconverted numeric characters, we prepend a â€˜#â€™ symbol to the converted values. In this way, for example, even after conversion, we can correctly distinguish between â€˜1ABCEFâ€™ and â€˜2ABCEFâ€™. Finally, as mentioned earlier, the vehicleâ€™s ID is generated by the license plate number and a hash function.
